<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-03-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-03-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="159" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d159">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thompson</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Rio de
                                    Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-03-12"><hi rend="italic">March 12, 1894</hi></date>.
                            (Received March 12.)</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Thompson reports that Saldanha da Gama has asked for amnesty for his
                        supporters and himself, and that the Portuguese commanding officer submitted
                        to the President in his behalf at 10 o’clock last night the terms under
                        which he offers to capitulate, and that the reply is expected to be returned
                        on this day.</p>
                </div>
